VIRGINIA FACILITY EXECUTIVE SUMMARY:  Doe and Ingalls of Virginia Operating, LLC facility, located at 5401 Lewis Road, Suite A in Sandston, Virginia occupies the western portion (approximately 28,000 sq. ft.) of a large commercial warehouse with one other tenant.  Doe and Ingalls of VA, LLC stores and distributes non-hazardous and hazardous chemicals to microelectronic customers within the region.  This summary will include the following elements:
1.    The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source;
2.    The stationary source and regulated substances handled;
3.    The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;
4.    The five-year accident history;
5.    The emergency response program; and;
6.    Planned changes to improve safety.
Adjacent and surrounding properties generally consist of a mix of light industrial, commercial and residential buildings.  Lewis Road is located west of the property with several commercial businesses further west.  A parking lot and hotel are located south of the property. East of the property is a storm water retention pond and an additional warehouse.  Reddy Ice plant is located north of the property with another storm water retention pond.  
The facility lies at approximately 160 feet above sea level and the topography can be characterized as urban/level.  The nearest natural water body to the property is an unnamed tributary to Gillie Creek located approximately ? mile north.  Storm water collected on the roof and precipitation leaves the property via one drop inlet located adjacent to the eastern portion of the warehouse, which is connected to the storm water retention pond.
The facility was constructed in 1997 specifically for chemical warehousing and Doe and Ingalls, LLC commenced operations in July 2001.  Prior to July 2001, the facility was leased to Great Western Chemical Company.  Doe and Ingalls, LLC employees are on-site 365 days per year operating from 7A
